      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773246013631,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Within a organization, noone can access outside from that organization.\nlike Bank need some space from their secret data or Colleges need private space to\nput the exam papers. and placement related stuff like that. Apart from specific set of\nuser noone else is allow to access this. Because hardware and all is setup by those people \nonly.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Within a organization, noone can access outside from that organization.\nlike Bank need some space from their secret data or Colleges need private space to\nput the exam papers. and placement related stuff like that. Apart from specific set of\nuser noone else is allow to access this. Because hardware and all is setup by those people \nonly.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "xTksVru53LLhwqPyfvcGU",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1166.0947957963417,
      "y": 36192.58107392791,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "baG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 608331325,
      "version": 694,
      "versionNonce": 1354287906,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773334417953,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q -> Public cloud anyone can use, suppose we have stored our File how they will make sure\n    only I can access that file noone else can't, due to Public cloud definition say anyone\n    can access? So which kind of security they provide?\n\n    Same like we have a public garden someone can go and do watering, someone can come and\n    destroy  that, someone can come and replace that with their own plant, then How we will\n    protect?\n\n    Q is like I have created one IAM instance and given root access and someone else also has created\n        IAM instance and given root access then why others can't see my instance detail ?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q -> Public cloud anyone can use, suppose we have stored our File how they will make sure\n    only I can access that file noone else can't, due to Public cloud definition say anyone\n    can access? So which kind of security they provide?\n\n    Same like we have a public garden someone can go and do watering, someone can come and\n    destroy  that, someone can come and replace that with their own plant, then How we will\n    protect?\n\n    Q is like I have created one IAM instance and given root access and someone else also has created\n        IAM instance and given root access then why others can't see my instance detail ?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "SoVMi9-Az8w9Zr2qfm4s4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1279.5010457963417,
      "y": 36455.29591767791,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "baH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1859302589,
      "version": 1124,
      "versionNonce": 1957018813,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773248115945,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Whenever  we want to use cloud first we make account, using that account whether we create\nresouce or not like Load balancers, EC2, storage like that but 1 resouce is by default\ncreated, which is called as Virtual Private Cloud(VPC). IN this space AWS says whatever we\nwill do, only we can access untill we don't allow others. As and when we will create more \nresource this VPC will increase, One VPC can't communicate with other VPC because virtually\nthey both are private. because they both behaving like a private cloud. To access these VPC\nwe need credentials like username and passsword. Root permission is also within this VPC only.\nboth VPC have their own Root. Both VPC resouce can communicate to each other with a secure\ntunnel but permission is required. VPC is more like a unique ID associated with our resource",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Whenever  we want to use cloud first we make account, using that account whether we create\nresouce or not like Load balancers, EC2, storage like that but 1 resouce is by default\ncreated, which is called as Virtual Private Cloud(VPC). IN this space AWS says whatever we\nwill do, only we can access untill we don't allow others. As and when we will create more \nresource this VPC will increase, One VPC can't communicate with other VPC because virtually\nthey both are private. because they both behaving like a private cloud. To access these VPC\nwe need credentials like username and passsword. Root permission is also within this VPC only.\nboth VPC have their own Root. Both VPC resouce can communicate to each other with a secure\ntunnel but permission is required. VPC is more like a unique ID associated with our resource",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "rMYcul7KTGVtU1ACbiTa-",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1279.4854207963417,
      "y": 36719.47169892791,
      "width": 605,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "baI",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1371734717,
      "version": 110,
      "versionNonce": 530349075,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773247969668,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q -> Why we need VPC, while we have our own Account ID?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q -> Why we need VPC, while we have our own Account ID?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6vBr6VZ3zXaC3LAbjFdao",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1328.3213582963417,
      "y": 36750.77248017791,
      "width": 847,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "baJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1058941939,
      "version": 180,
      "versionNonce": 1791907731,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773248098954,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "because one AccountID can have multiple VPCs, like stage and prod and dev VPC",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "because one AccountID can have multiple VPCs, like stage and prod and dev VPC",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
