      "versionNonce": 933693218,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776274782162,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "second imp thing that we have in cloud is User.\nwe have created our own AWS account fot that we have created our Account, One account can have\nmultiple user created also.\n\nSuppose I am making Linux socials account and for all my developers I will make Linux socials \ncloud account or I will make them the subpart of my own account. Second approach where in I am\nmaking a User within my own cloud account so that all of those users can access my AWS cloud\nthat becomes more managable, more easy that is what we do\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "second imp thing that we have in cloud is User.\nwe have created our own AWS account fot that we have created our Account, One account can have\nmultiple user created also.\n\nSuppose I am making Linux socials account and for all my developers I will make Linux socials \ncloud account or I will make them the subpart of my own account. Second approach where in I am\nmaking a User within my own cloud account so that all of those users can access my AWS cloud\nthat becomes more managable, more easy that is what we do\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "yTCfed85UOXm-pteEwN5j",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1152.286202046342,
      "y": 43651.77833955291,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
