tance and we \n    want to assign public IP to it. or if we want to block a public IP for ourself even without creating \n    a instance. they will allow us to get or have public IPs. They would not charge to us untill and unless\n    we are using it with the instance. they will only charge us when we are blocking a IP or when we are\n    keeping the IP to ourself without attaching it to a instance.\n\n    Why it is a great business trick? -> \n       It looks like they are giving something as free when we are using it but this is not free. becuase to \n        use this IP we have to use it with the instance. Means first we need to create instance that money\n        we need to keep on running that instance we need to pay for that\n        Now we have IP and users and everything, Users will come to us via IP, So they will charge us on\n        network bandwidth's incoming and outgoing of our resources. they will charge us on that like howmuch\n        data transaction is there. howmuch data is transferring they will charge us on that.\n        So they earn not by making sure that they have given us a public IP but making sure that they create\n        a mechanism where we constantly use a public IP address.\n\n    \n    \n    Now we can set firewall rule like allow it from anywhere in the world, From anywhere in world allow \n    everyone to SSH, everyone to connect on HTTP, everyone to connect on HTTPS if and only if they have\n    the key. because there is a key based login.\n    For SSH there is key based logoi for HTTP and HTTPs anyways they can reach out.\n\nNext we need to configure Storage -> \n    what HDD we need, if we want to attach a additional HDD we can attach over there, they will attach something\n    as sdb.\n\nthese are required for now, we will talk other details also when we advance the concept of VMs.\n\nNow after launching instance, once status check is done, now to connect with this system there are few way\nwe can either use pem file using our linux terminal, if we are in windows there are softwares called as\nputty, we can use this software that will give us a terminal from where we can connect to our AWS intance.\nor there are softwares like mobaxterm we can use this also it can allow us to run multiple session at\nthe similar time on the same EC2 also.\nEasiest way is connect direcly via browser using the feature that AWS provides to us. we can connect via\nssh or we can connect direcly via EC2 instance connect(click on connect on the instance), and hit connect\nand now we can see this will open terminal directly. this is the same Ubuntu terminal that we get in VM.\nEC2 is not only about creating VMs.\n\nNow delete the instance\n    instance state ->     terminate(delete) instance\n\n\nNow we will talk about few interesting services that we will talk about, we can see that instances is one of\nthe service that comes under the hood of EC2, But there are other services also which are very imp one.",
