      "updated": 1773747190208,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Spot Request -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Spot Request -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "J_i1JlWz0DkVw86n7ZUBT",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1348.122139546342,
      "y": 48416.02443330291,
      "width": 1144,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bcu",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 464696138,
      "version": 438,
      "versionNonce": 289998358,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773747540610,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Spot Request (It is also same like a VM), we can see this with all other instances. Even a equally\npowerful instance will cost us just 0.3 or regular price, which means 70% less cost from regular\ninstance cost. because instances are on demand instance which we need that. but spot request we need\non spot because may be we have some extra resources. it might be go down just with 2 minute notification\nif someone ask for VM thats why its price less",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Spot Request (It is also same like a VM), we can see this with all other instances. Even a equally\npowerful instance will cost us just 0.3 or regular price, which means 70% less cost from regular\ninstance cost. because instances are on demand instance which we need that. but spot request we need\non spot because may be we have some extra resources. it might be go down just with 2 minute notification\nif someone ask for VM thats why its price less",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3nsRCE_nnWvOY6rsNDOOv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1288.829170796342,
      "y": 48619.19630830291,
      "width": 319,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bcv",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 113440918,
      "version": 38,
      "versionNonce": 619526166,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773747569410,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "AMI(Amazon Machine Image) -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "AMI(Amazon Machine Image) -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "sOGpPXKKh-296bC1uJcXt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1341.149483296342,
      "y": 48661.85646455291,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bcx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1011199894,
      "version": 266,
      "versionNonce": 222199690,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773747697148,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Right now to create a instance we choose ubuntu, So ubuntu is a image that they are providing us \nubuntu AMI. Likewise we can create our own AMIs, images like Linuxsocial dev AMI, Linuxsocial prod ami\nLinuxsocial test ami and so on. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Right now to create a instance we choose ubuntu, So ubuntu is a image that they are providing us \nubuntu AMI. Likewise we can create our own AMIs, images like Linuxsocial dev AMI, Linuxsocial prod ami\nLinuxsocial test ami and so on. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "yrdY11qT82POlYKkdcHbU",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1342.848702046342,
      "y": 48774.53224580291,
      "width": 594,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bcy",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 177710346,
      "version": 73,
      "versionNonce": 373545866,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773747766424,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is the usecase of creating our own image (AMI) ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is the usecase of creating our own image (AMI) ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "7TDiJIjpdo9MXkaMO59zo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1386.430733296342,
      "y": 48815.38380830291,
      "width": 1188,
      "height": 525,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bd0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 519438602,
      "version": 1840,
      "versionNonce": 731882698,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773748578459,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Company creates our own Golden/Base AMI \nGolden/Base AMI  -> \n    When a company starts setting its whole new AWS infra, lets say they started from today, So what\n  they will do, they will launch a ubuntu based instance from this whatever software they want, their\norganization not support or not have they will remove those softwares suppose this is not done.\nthey will add softwares like some firewall tools, they want that whatever new system is now created, it\nshould directly connect to my monitoring server. So they will connect this system with their monitoring\nserver. then then will pack this into a AMI.\n\nNow if I want to create any type of software/applicatin like I want to create my own web server, So it \nwill be just told to me that I can only use one AMI to launch a new system, I can launch any number of \nsystems. But the restriction is we can use one particular AMI.\n\nAnd now when I am using this AMI, I am making sure this is secure. why security is installed it has all\ncompany level level that it needed, Because they were there in the AMI also, I am making sure that this\nsystem automatically connects with my monitoring server. Because AMI automatically connected with the\nmonitoring system. Not the AMI but the system from which we have created the AMI already connected with\nthe monitoring server. So I am making sure our system is autoconnected with monitoring.\n\nIt is more like we have instance we have packed with our own softwares. So this is the AMI so our developers\nwill create from this AMI. benefit is all the softwares that organization needed already there.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Company creates our own Golden/Base AMI \nGolden/Base AMI  -> \n    When a company starts setting its whole new AWS infra, lets say they started from today, So what\n  they will do, they will launch a ubuntu based instance from this whatever software they want, their\norganization not support or not have they will remove those softwares suppose this is not done.\nthey will add softwares like some firewall tools, they want that whatever new system is now created, it\nshould directly connect to my monitoring server. So they will connect this system with their monitoring\nserver. then then will pack this into a AMI.\n\nNow if I want to create any type of software/applicatin like I want to create my own web server, So it \nwill be just told to me that I can only use one AMI to launch a new system, I can launch any number of \nsystems. But the restriction is we can use one particular AMI.\n\nAnd now when I am using this AMI, I am making sure this is secure. why security is installed it has all\ncompany level level that it needed, Because they were there in the AMI also, I am making sure that this\nsystem automatically connects with my monitoring server. Because AMI automatically connected with the\nmonitoring system. Not the AMI but the system from which we have created the AMI already connected with\nthe monitoring server. So I am making sure our system is autoconnected with monitoring.\n\nIt is more like we have instance we have packed with our own softwares. So this is the AMI so our developers\nwill create from this AMI. benefit is all the softwares that organization needed already there.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
