    {
      "id": "6QbgTefflIoDXdy3E2KhH",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1389.305733296342,
      "y": 51919.96193330291,
      "width": 1078,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bdJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1956796502,
      "version": 1098,
      "versionNonce": 23162314,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773755891587,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It is restricted because of security reasons, whom we will allow only that can come, PORT\n22 is always has to be allowed , because when we are doing testing on our system or we are\nin dev phase, we have to ssh again and again. but when we deploy our application in production\nFor example we have this web server and we deploy it on production now we dont need to do ssh \nagain and again and we dont want any security risks also, In that case when we have deploy our\ncode in production, when everything is set then we can remove PORT 22 so that no one can come\nand ssh to our system and start working on our system, then we can remove it. Otherwise dont \nremove PORT 22\n\nPORT 80\nwhen we do http://public ip we are not giving port no where.\nbut by giving http protocol over here, http protocol by default works on port number 80, though we\ncan change it but it is default port for http.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It is restricted because of security reasons, whom we will allow only that can come, PORT\n22 is always has to be allowed , because when we are doing testing on our system or we are\nin dev phase, we have to ssh again and again. but when we deploy our application in production\nFor example we have this web server and we deploy it on production now we dont need to do ssh \nagain and again and we dont want any security risks also, In that case when we have deploy our\ncode in production, when everything is set then we can remove PORT 22 so that no one can come\nand ssh to our system and start working on our system, then we can remove it. Otherwise dont \nremove PORT 22\n\nPORT 80\nwhen we do http://public ip we are not giving port no where.\nbut by giving http protocol over here, http protocol by default works on port number 80, though we\ncan change it but it is default port for http.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8yo1EV4u4Se0CvliRnosn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1274.567452046342,
      "y": 52321.50880830291,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bdM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 578025558,
      "version": 690,
      "versionNonce": 1786126730,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773770061255,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now do \ncd /var/www/html \nls -> it will give index.html\n    this location is automatically gets created, when we start or when we install and start our web\n    server, so webserver by default created our own defaul index.html page we can completely delete\n    or modify this index.html\n\nsudo vi index.html -> if we will only do vi index.html then we will not able to do write on this file\nesc :%d -> it will delete content\ni -> insert\nesc :wq! -> save and exit\nHello then we will see hello instead of Apache page\n\nif we dont want to put index.html, we can put our whole application here also",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now do \ncd /var/www/html \nls -> it will give index.html\n    this location is automatically gets created, when we start or when we install and start our web\n    server, so webserver by default created our own defaul index.html page we can completely delete\n    or modify this index.html\n\nsudo vi index.html -> if we will only do vi index.html then we will not able to do write on this file\nesc :%d -> it will delete content\ni -> insert\nesc :wq! -> save and exit\nHello then we will see hello instead of Apache page\n\nif we dont want to put index.html, we can put our whole application here also",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fU__cVZ-kYFBfPAnBE4wt",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1638.094795796342,
      "y": 52844.64162080291,
      "width": 130.58203125,
