      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bdl",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1561310934,
      "version": 24,
      "versionNonce": 1371207574,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773771439138,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Vertical Scaling -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Vertical Scaling -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ScK7FJSpYXqqbCFVg5pfu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1041.715889546342,
      "y": 53791.49708955291,
      "width": 1056,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bdm",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1603852118,
      "version": 259,
      "versionNonce": 1823708618,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773771551471,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If we will do things in single instance, and we are continuously having increasing, increasing\nnumber of users coming, one thing we can do is we can make the system more powerful or even more\npowerful. but there is a limit to it",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If we will do things in single instance, and we are continuously having increasing, increasing\nnumber of users coming, one thing we can do is we can make the system more powerful or even more\npowerful. but there is a limit to it",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "psawYl91A1PF_3sabHAQc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1044.211983296342,
      "y": 53907.00490205291,
      "width": 539,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bdn",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 884377174,
      "version": 53,
      "versionNonce": 1490790026,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773771581807,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why there is a limit to it? what are the problems",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why there is a limit to it? what are the problems",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PZQcDeCI3u7k6hGRy_Fup",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1054.383858296342,
      "y": 53955.78615205291,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bdo",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1731136598,
      "version": 1467,
      "versionNonce": 1774226272,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773827987124,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1 Problem 1 is there is a limit.\n2 Cost management\n\nwhich things make system a powerful system -> hardware in terms of HDD, Network, RAM, and to \n    process users we need processor\n\nHDD\nNetwork\nRAM\nProcessor\n\nNow the thing is we can add HDD, as we want, we can add infinite HDD.\nWE can have a terrabyte speed wala network connection super fast, so that is also extremely good.\nRAM. also we can expand infinte. according to HDD(TB), we can add few gbs or RAM.\n\nRAM works like a buffer for our processor. So that processor can fetch from there. But processor\nhas a limit, based on whatever scientific inventions are done.\nHm kitna hi mhnga processor le lenge(i5, i7, MAC chip) etc, for deploying web server hm quantom\nchip to lagaenge ni. So this is where we have a blocker. This is why everywhere we have a blocker.\nSo not just processor, because of this everywhere we have a blocker that this scaling is limited.\nthis type of scaling in whihc we keep on scaling one single system and keep on making it more heavy,\nThis is called as Vertical Scaling, where we are putting resources on single instance and we\nare making that single system powerful.(37:30)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 Problem 1 is there is a limit.\n2 Cost management\n\nwhich things make system a powerful system -> hardware in terms of HDD, Network, RAM, and to \n    process users we need processor\n\nHDD\nNetwork\nRAM\nProcessor\n\nNow the thing is we can add HDD, as we want, we can add infinite HDD.\nWE can have a terrabyte speed wala network connection super fast, so that is also extremely good.\nRAM. also we can expand infinte. according to HDD(TB), we can add few gbs or RAM.\n\nRAM works like a buffer for our processor. So that processor can fetch from there. But processor\nhas a limit, based on whatever scientific inventions are done.\nHm kitna hi mhnga processor le lenge(i5, i7, MAC chip) etc, for deploying web server hm quantom\nchip to lagaenge ni. So this is where we have a blocker. This is why everywhere we have a blocker.\nSo not just processor, because of this everywhere we have a blocker that this scaling is limited.\nthis type of scaling in whihc we keep on scaling one single system and keep on making it more heavy,\nThis is called as Vertical Scaling, where we are putting resources on single instance and we\nare making that single system powerful.(37:30)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
