      "seed": 735104672,
      "version": 931,
      "versionNonce": 528214880,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773831812044,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "we always use both together\n\nLets say Google has to launch servers, they can't do like this that we will launch 1 million t2.micro\nservers. who will launch these many instances or monitoring or health check.\n\nSo first of all we will increase capacity of t2.micro lets say we will make it i4x, then rather than\nlaunching 1 million t2.micro we will launch 10K i4x, so this is more sensible.\nhence this is how we balance by first scaling it or finding a right fit of the instance body type.\nOnce we find it right fit, after that we will Load Balance it as per our need.\n\nIN terms of Auto & Manual scaling what we use ->\n    Auto Scaling hm lga k rkhte h, but there are always unpredictable situations like in a week definetly\nonce, So at that time we have to do manual scaling also.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "we always use both together\n\nLets say Google has to launch servers, they can't do like this that we will launch 1 million t2.micro\nservers. who will launch these many instances or monitoring or health check.\n\nSo first of all we will increase capacity of t2.micro lets say we will make it i4x, then rather than\nlaunching 1 million t2.micro we will launch 10K i4x, so this is more sensible.\nhence this is how we balance by first scaling it or finding a right fit of the instance body type.\nOnce we find it right fit, after that we will Load Balance it as per our need.\n\nIN terms of Auto & Manual scaling what we use ->\n    Auto Scaling hm lga k rkhte h, but there are always unpredictable situations like in a week definetly\nonce, So at that time we have to do manual scaling also.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
