      "updated": 1773833937093,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What if my LB goes down?\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What if my LB goes down?\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "7JXv93GBtFw4CZubNsBum",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1142.3741328644128,
      "y": 60711.487670894414,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bf1",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1301409632,
      "version": 846,
      "versionNonce": 233208672,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773833957027,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Single Point Of Failure\nEC2 and LB both services are provided by cloud, but these are different , EC2 is generic service\nwhere as LB is managed service.\n\nthat means LB functionalities like Routing, like shell never go down, that should always be up and\nrunning, that should always keep on working, the responsibility of that is taken directly by \ncloud Provider. So we dont have to worry about this as this a managed service but we have to create\nand use for the functionality, there are other managed services also, like databases RDS or Dynamo\nthese are also managed by AWS. hence we need to worry about SPOF",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Single Point Of Failure\nEC2 and LB both services are provided by cloud, but these are different , EC2 is generic service\nwhere as LB is managed service.\n\nthat means LB functionalities like Routing, like shell never go down, that should always be up and\nrunning, that should always keep on working, the responsibility of that is taken directly by \ncloud Provider. So we dont have to worry about this as this a managed service but we have to create\nand use for the functionality, there are other managed services also, like databases RDS or Dynamo\nthese are also managed by AWS. hence we need to worry about SPOF",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
