    {
      "id": "SfDlowOT3vFnvmYXsoJ-c",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1120.8636862610665,
      "y": 61264.15306330539,
      "width": 1177,
      "height": 650,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bf6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1277204320,
      "version": 1874,
      "versionNonce": 284854112,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773839455560,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "till now we have deployes on frontend is just a basic HTML page. but application is not simple \nmost of the time our webpages dynamic.\nDynamic webpages in which data is designed on runtime.\nif we open amazon it looks different to me and it lookds different to other as it is listing product\non basis of previous searches.\n\nIRCTC home page looks similar to everyone so that homepage is static page.\n\nBest example of static website is our own portfolio website. It will look same to everyone. They have\nbasically static webpage using HTML, CSS, Bootstrap and some media(images or videos or files) content\nlets say 1 GB of media.\n\n1 way is we can put this 1 GB media in every instance, the problem this can give us, that when we doing\npackagin or containerasing our application or we are making a new OS AMI and then pacakaging, however we\nare packaging that is going to slow and that is going to be heavy. Heavy because of this 1 GB extra data.\n\nSo what is the second approach we can use, we can have a EBS(external HDD) attached to all our instances\nand that EBS has this 1 GB data. which means more costing on EBS as we need to attach on all the instances.\n\nSo simple solution here is have a common storage and this common storage will be link to all of our\ninstances.\n\nExample -> lets say we have to display some images on our website, Images we can fetch via the link also, \nso those link we can put on Google drive, we can make them publically accesible and then we can use these\nlinks over here, that is one way, A similar service within our AWS cloud plateform if we have to use\nit is called as S3.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "till now we have deployes on frontend is just a basic HTML page. but application is not simple \nmost of the time our webpages dynamic.\nDynamic webpages in which data is designed on runtime.\nif we open amazon it looks different to me and it lookds different to other as it is listing product\non basis of previous searches.\n\nIRCTC home page looks similar to everyone so that homepage is static page.\n\nBest example of static website is our own portfolio website. It will look same to everyone. They have\nbasically static webpage using HTML, CSS, Bootstrap and some media(images or videos or files) content\nlets say 1 GB of media.\n\n1 way is we can put this 1 GB media in every instance, the problem this can give us, that when we doing\npackagin or containerasing our application or we are making a new OS AMI and then pacakaging, however we\nare packaging that is going to slow and that is going to be heavy. Heavy because of this 1 GB extra data.\n\nSo what is the second approach we can use, we can have a EBS(external HDD) attached to all our instances\nand that EBS has this 1 GB data. which means more costing on EBS as we need to attach on all the instances.\n\nSo simple solution here is have a common storage and this common storage will be link to all of our\ninstances.\n\nExample -> lets say we have to display some images on our website, Images we can fetch via the link also, \nso those link we can put on Google drive, we can make them publically accesible and then we can use these\nlinks over here, that is one way, A similar service within our AWS cloud plateform if we have to use\nit is called as S3.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "oEtcxGCr4fbjQKJ6EUMou",
