    {
      "id": "5YU6nk0GULzeg2Z0HaZKf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1092.2328108003367,
      "y": 64450.215254811315,
      "width": 1199,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bgP",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1166319456,
      "version": 1250,
      "versionNonce": 1723475616,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773849155977,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1 option is having EC2 instance\n2 option is why we create IAAS why not we use PASS service\n    Example -> we just need the code to verify whether the ID and password are matching from what is\n        there in database or not, Do we need entire OS level control here -> No\n        Do we need any control on HDD partitioning or any control on lets say we need 2 3 diff software\n        to be setup and then only our login verification code run -> No, nothing like this so what we can do\n        is that we can write a simple Javascript code and connect via that and this is done using any PAAS\n        where in we can just write and execute the code. And whenever the backend is called at that time our\n        function will start running. This is called as Lambda. And lot of our microservice are written like \n        this in any microservice architecture. There is not just one lambda, there can be multiple lambdas,\n        and we can route these multiple lambdas to one lambda or to diff lambda or third lambda, we can route\n        based on what kind of request is there.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 option is having EC2 instance\n2 option is why we create IAAS why not we use PASS service\n    Example -> we just need the code to verify whether the ID and password are matching from what is\n        there in database or not, Do we need entire OS level control here -> No\n        Do we need any control on HDD partitioning or any control on lets say we need 2 3 diff software\n        to be setup and then only our login verification code run -> No, nothing like this so what we can do\n        is that we can write a simple Javascript code and connect via that and this is done using any PAAS\n        where in we can just write and execute the code. And whenever the backend is called at that time our\n        function will start running. This is called as Lambda. And lot of our microservice are written like \n        this in any microservice architecture. There is not just one lambda, there can be multiple lambdas,\n        and we can route these multiple lambdas to one lambda or to diff lambda or third lambda, we can route\n        based on what kind of request is there.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "x00s7amsARbrPkJ7VNcaY",
