      "index": "bhL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 25994912,
      "version": 109,
      "versionNonce": 1619438432,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773851356981,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What we can improve on this existing system? What are the flaw in this?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What we can improve on this existing system? What are the flaw in this?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "9qppudeltrtdmPTC0XPur",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1329.3619330183574,
      "y": 66309.10644247453,
      "width": 1177,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bhM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 849040224,
      "version": 1410,
      "versionNonce": 423516000,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773851949664,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why we need Kernel again, when we have this Linux kernel already\nwhy do we need same Utility S/W, when we have the Utility S/W\nwhy do we need same Application S/W, when we have the Application S/W\nAt best we need minimun set of binaries becuase these binary give a feel like Ubuntu or there will be\na diff set of binaries that will give file like RHEL so diff is all about Binaries that is playing the\ngame. Remaining everything else is same.\n\nSo what if I do something like this, we have a kernel on Base, we have there utility and applicatoin \nS/W over here on top of this we have a Hypervisor but this Hypervisor says that whatever you want to \nshare from Base like if you want to use a shared kernel you can use, If you want to use shared applications\nyou can use, and you can just give me bare minimum set of binaries and on top of this because everything\nelse is shared, I will give a isolated space just like the VM is creating isolated space, this will also\ngive us a isolated space but with the shared resource\n\nEven if we have RHEL as base, we can just use binary of ubuntu to take a look and feel of ubuntu, and we \ncan deploy web server or anything here in Ubuntu, this is architecture of Container.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why we need Kernel again, when we have this Linux kernel already\nwhy do we need same Utility S/W, when we have the Utility S/W\nwhy do we need same Application S/W, when we have the Application S/W\nAt best we need minimun set of binaries becuase these binary give a feel like Ubuntu or there will be\na diff set of binaries that will give file like RHEL so diff is all about Binaries that is playing the\ngame. Remaining everything else is same.\n\nSo what if I do something like this, we have a kernel on Base, we have there utility and applicatoin \nS/W over here on top of this we have a Hypervisor but this Hypervisor says that whatever you want to \nshare from Base like if you want to use a shared kernel you can use, If you want to use shared applications\nyou can use, and you can just give me bare minimum set of binaries and on top of this because everything\nelse is shared, I will give a isolated space just like the VM is creating isolated space, this will also\ngive us a isolated space but with the shared resource\n\nEven if we have RHEL as base, we can just use binary of ubuntu to take a look and feel of ubuntu, and we \ncan deploy web server or anything here in Ubuntu, this is architecture of Container.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
