    {
      "id": "lRBceLakEADVNHXT-IGnc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2122.316285150085,
      "y": 67694.54799008157,
      "width": 616,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bia",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1752069792,
      "version": 427,
      "versionNonce": 537836192,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773852744690,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This Hypervisor playes\na diff purpose here, this\nhypervisor says that I will\nshare that base wale resources\n\nTo create your isolated space, You just have to\ninstall some basic bare minimum binaries, And on top\nof these binaries now we can deploy any application that\nwe want. This is the architecture of Docker Container.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This Hypervisor playes\na diff purpose here, this\nhypervisor says that I will\nshare that base wale resources\n\nTo create your isolated space, You just have to\ninstall some basic bare minimum binaries, And on top\nof these binaries now we can deploy any application that\nwe want. This is the architecture of Docker Container.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kxOh06-6VgDT_LXv0uulP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1450.4131488578869,
      "y": 68134.62111052708,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bib",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 152752992,
      "version": 585,
      "versionNonce": 1726711648,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773852851918,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Container are not as powerful as the VM. Because in the VM all the things in its own space, It is\nnot shared, we can do a lot of modifications over here. We can do lot of kernel level modifications\nover here. We can also do lot of modifications on Utillity and Applicatin S/W over here also.\nSo there is restriction on Docker container on what is the level of modification we can do. But at\nthe same time in VM there is no such restriction. Because they bring their own resource.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Container are not as powerful as the VM. Because in the VM all the things in its own space, It is\nnot shared, we can do a lot of modifications over here. We can do lot of kernel level modifications\nover here. We can also do lot of modifications on Utillity and Applicatin S/W over here also.\nSo there is restriction on Docker container on what is the level of modification we can do. But at\nthe same time in VM there is no such restriction. Because they bring their own resource.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
