    {
      "id": "t4AVAUDar0njQwP-9Aj8s",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1344.6252954899828,
      "y": 68772.6849151614,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bj4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 729338720,
      "version": 133,
      "versionNonce": 2043961184,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773857581608,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q -> If we have these VMs then why we even need these containers and Docker? When we can't even\n    modify them",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q -> If we have these VMs then why we even need these containers and Docker? When we can't even\n    modify them",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pid5xTK9kjjg5qmVTqZf_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1420.5237329899828,
      "y": 68842.8138214114,
      "width": 946,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bj5",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1993612128,
      "version": 179,
      "versionNonce": 1120976736,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773857700118,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "when docker came, Container got accepted across the industry, everyone loved using it.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "when docker came, Container got accepted across the industry, everyone loved using it.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "x_esYxztaGuRzrkJctUEr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1425.5823267399828,
      "y": 68891.4388214114,
      "width": 979,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bj6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1862242976,
      "version": 102,
      "versionNonce": 236974944,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773857806973,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is the reason behind this? or Why we are using Docker even if this has less control?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is the reason behind this? or Why we are using Docker even if this has less control?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dNHLBz3tbrIRdeOOwVniW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1453.4495142399828,
      "y": 68931.6185089114,
      "width": 1188,
      "height": 750,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bj7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 813865824,
      "version": 2063,
      "versionNonce": 160935776,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773858880255,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "when we have created VMs\nHDD needed -> 20-25 GB\nRAM needed -> 4 to 8 GB\ntime needed for this -> 5 to 20 minutes\n\nFor containers\nthere is no compulsion of HDD, it can run entirely like a process on RAM also. there is no\\\ncompulsion on HDD, but whatever shared HDD we need, we can take that\nContainers can run just in around 10 MBs, Imagine howmany isolated environment we can run.\ntime estimation to running a container is barely is 1 to 2 sec.\nThis is only possible due to redundancy(reinstalling kernel, Utility, Application S/W) that is not happening\nwe just need to set bare minimum just basic binaries and we are done.\n\nFor container Docker is not first software, Docker came very late in market. before that there is already\nsomething called as LXC(Linux Container), but container becomes famous only after Docker launched.\nContainer we can also think of it as a process.\nSo to create this process we have to put some entries or make some entries into multiple files at\nmultiple places and multiple input and also sometime same input at multiple places, multiple commands\n\nOne command is to setup the network\nAnother command to setup the file system\nAnother command to create the container\nso many commands but the same input\n\nto bnde ne kya kiye,he read the code of all these commands got them all together in a single command\nor in single code, and now he is like that whenever you need inputs, you just give me the inputs, if this\nrequired at multiple places my code will automatically give it. And that is why Docker came into picture.\nThought LXC was already there, they packages better way and better managed that visualizing container is \nDocker for us.\nNow a days every company using Docker.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "when we have created VMs\nHDD needed -> 20-25 GB\nRAM needed -> 4 to 8 GB\ntime needed for this -> 5 to 20 minutes\n\nFor containers\nthere is no compulsion of HDD, it can run entirely like a process on RAM also. there is no\\\ncompulsion on HDD, but whatever shared HDD we need, we can take that\nContainers can run just in around 10 MBs, Imagine howmany isolated environment we can run.\ntime estimation to running a container is barely is 1 to 2 sec.\nThis is only possible due to redundancy(reinstalling kernel, Utility, Application S/W) that is not happening\nwe just need to set bare minimum just basic binaries and we are done.\n\nFor container Docker is not first software, Docker came very late in market. before that there is already\nsomething called as LXC(Linux Container), but container becomes famous only after Docker launched.\nContainer we can also think of it as a process.\nSo to create this process we have to put some entries or make some entries into multiple files at\nmultiple places and multiple input and also sometime same input at multiple places, multiple commands\n\nOne command is to setup the network\nAnother command to setup the file system\nAnother command to create the container\nso many commands but the same input\n\nto bnde ne kya kiye,he read the code of all these commands got them all together in a single command\nor in single code, and now he is like that whenever you need inputs, you just give me the inputs, if this\nrequired at multiple places my code will automatically give it. And that is why Docker came into picture.\nThought LXC was already there, they packages better way and better managed that visualizing container is \nDocker for us.\nNow a days every company using Docker.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
