      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775922895462,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Backend Instance\nwe hav two choices",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Backend Instance\nwe hav two choices",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6dLb7ce48fOLbXJKB5W0c",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1965.9618838429342,
      "y": 70126.2992023067,
      "width": 275,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjg",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 63771876,
      "version": 72,
      "versionNonce": 983506276,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775922888128,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "EC2 instance(complete VM)\nOR\nContainer",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "EC2 instance(complete VM)\nOR\nContainer",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "7wLiRF7XQKrOdCAkil1td",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1315.3052009712433,
      "y": 70749.75008747775,
      "width": 506,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjh",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1989095780,
      "version": 77,
      "versionNonce": 1034764636,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775922932772,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When we choose a VM and when we use Container?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When we choose a VM and when we use Container?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8KlOjJG2XMOJnj64rX3sk",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1341.9324518386215,
      "y": 70781.34674460284,
      "width": 1210,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bji",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1233069540,
      "version": 1520,
      "versionNonce": 475760612,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962036912,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We use VM when we need first of all a heavy machine, which means the code that is running is heavy, It is\nresouce intensive. Secondly there are multiple application which are working together to produce a single\nresult, So rather than having multiple applications all installed in a single container which is not \nsuppose to be a very good idea, So if there are multiple application we preffer having a whole OS, where\nin we can do each of these things. Also we might need good control over RAM, on our HDD, on our OS, the\nenv variables, the way OS is behaving, the way variuos tools are installed in OS. We might need a deeper\ncontrol on that. For this purpose we go for whole virtualized or VM environment.\n\nIf Backend code is simple not require too much of OS envolvement, then we can go for a container. But we have\nanother usecase that we see we dont need at all OS level control or whats going on in Operating Sytem, we dont\nneed to install things or multiple softwares or even few softwares, what we need is just a coding environment,\nAnd in that coding environment if we are going to code something, what will happend whenever the code will \ncalled, It is going to run and produce the result. So that kind of functionality are usually written in lambda\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We use VM when we need first of all a heavy machine, which means the code that is running is heavy, It is\nresouce intensive. Secondly there are multiple application which are working together to produce a single\nresult, So rather than having multiple applications all installed in a single container which is not \nsuppose to be a very good idea, So if there are multiple application we preffer having a whole OS, where\nin we can do each of these things. Also we might need good control over RAM, on our HDD, on our OS, the\nenv variables, the way OS is behaving, the way variuos tools are installed in OS. We might need a deeper\ncontrol on that. For this purpose we go for whole virtualized or VM environment.\n\nIf Backend code is simple not require too much of OS envolvement, then we can go for a container. But we have\nanother usecase that we see we dont need at all OS level control or whats going on in Operating Sytem, we dont\nneed to install things or multiple softwares or even few softwares, what we need is just a coding environment,\nAnd in that coding environment if we are going to code something, what will happend whenever the code will \ncalled, It is going to run and produce the result. So that kind of functionality are usually written in lambda\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BysJsWwfW6uN797Ju5xRl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1337.9994846446386,
      "y": 71148.2656008666,
      "width": 187,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjj",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2029996636,
      "version": 24,
      "versionNonce": 271840860,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962056007,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is Lambda ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is Lambda ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WKV_zxxaqKhiCjrRBPqaE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1377.10838711621,
      "y": 71182.53392833019,
      "width": 1177,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjk",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 831447268,
      "version": 566,
      "versionNonce": 253061476,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962268935,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Lambda behaves as a serverless architecture, it provide us a coding plateform, via load balance we can also\nhit one or multiple lambdas that we create, based on whatever API is called it will redirect to specific\nlambda, Now the lambda will run the code and produce the result. Lambda is already assigned with some RAM,\nsome CPU, not any specific HDD, because HDD is not needed here, if HDD is needed, or that level of control\nneeded we will either move to EC2 or a container",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Lambda behaves as a serverless architecture, it provide us a coding plateform, via load balance we can also\nhit one or multiple lambdas that we create, based on whatever API is called it will redirect to specific\nlambda, Now the lambda will run the code and produce the result. Lambda is already assigned with some RAM,\nsome CPU, not any specific HDD, because HDD is not needed here, if HDD is needed, or that level of control\nneeded we will either move to EC2 or a container",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zAhOlqs1G1-cgHig-dEZy",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1339.6102840983078,
      "y": 71410.54990091945,
      "width": 341,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjl",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 751657060,
      "version": 38,
      "versionNonce": 1033638372,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962312454,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Third Layer (Database Layer) ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Third Layer (Database Layer) ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
