    },
    {
      "id": "ykVPlGDLNxWWNOsXKnOfI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1989.5147154484876,
      "y": 71567.00395732126,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjw",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 645367004,
      "version": 129,
      "versionNonce": 1749600604,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962534416,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "there is no issue of scaling, we will add one more\ninstance, there is no issue of SPOF as LB is self\nmanaged service.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "there is no issue of scaling, we will add one more\ninstance, there is no issue of SPOF as LB is self\nmanaged service.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "0y8wMvwB-VRP0P4kXWoQK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1422.0227089385687,
      "y": 71993.2995306808,
      "width": 715,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1343616228,
      "version": 92,
      "versionNonce": 995064156,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962611855,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q If all the DBs having same data, then are we going to scale it?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q If all the DBs having same data, then are we going to scale it?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "M0J-oq8Csj50OTRh2TIQw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1429.6474322408353,
      "y": 72074.67152625365,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjy",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 575525468,
      "version": 166,
      "versionNonce": 328817372,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962680420,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "databases doesn't work like a system, they have their own properties of a good DB, A good DB follows\nsomething called as ACID properties.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "databases doesn't work like a system, they have their own properties of a good DB, A good DB follows\nsomething called as ACID properties.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zkJ3yND7gDM-koSj8V9t1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1429.54931247716,
      "y": 72143.24088776871,
      "width": 330,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjz",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 427346788,
      "version": 41,
      "versionNonce": 822151908,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775962720988,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Practical Scenerio/ Analogy ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Practical Scenerio/ Analogy ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pBhKSFuLeTagUbuuY4xIt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1488.5029371520563,
      "y": 72186.20298606638,
      "width": 1177,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 767549020,
      "version": 1506,
      "versionNonce": 720712036,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775963536571,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "lets say we make a Bank transaction, when we are making a banking transaction, we go to a bank\nand make a transaction at the same time we give someone our ATM card and ask them do a transaction\nat a very same time so we are planning a heist now\nLets say ATM guy hit some other server of Bank and I or bank hit another server, we both are redirected\nto backend, in the backend lets say we have 1 cr in account, so in all the DBs its showing 1Cr , We both\nare redirected to diff backend server, now we both hit the Database LB to withdraw 1 Cr and somehow we both\nare redirected to lets say different databases which is very high possibility, Now in that case what will \nhappen we are able to withdraw 2 Cr but in account we originally have 1 Cr, there is a problem like this.\n\nthere can be only one DB, Do we have multiple DB at any point of time -> It is suppose to be, it should\nbe only one DB. So having multiple DB is not a good approach, when we will see at company scale we usually\nhave 1 database, Now problem with having a single DB, If there is only one DB then again there is a similar\nproblem that we were facing with single instance that there are millions of requests and if there are\nmillions of request then this DB will crash. again there is a issue. So we can't have a single DB also.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "lets say we make a Bank transaction, when we are making a banking transaction, we go to a bank\nand make a transaction at the same time we give someone our ATM card and ask them do a transaction\nat a very same time so we are planning a heist now\nLets say ATM guy hit some other server of Bank and I or bank hit another server, we both are redirected\nto backend, in the backend lets say we have 1 cr in account, so in all the DBs its showing 1Cr , We both\nare redirected to diff backend server, now we both hit the Database LB to withdraw 1 Cr and somehow we both\nare redirected to lets say different databases which is very high possibility, Now in that case what will \nhappen we are able to withdraw 2 Cr but in account we originally have 1 Cr, there is a problem like this.\n\nthere can be only one DB, Do we have multiple DB at any point of time -> It is suppose to be, it should\nbe only one DB. So having multiple DB is not a good approach, when we will see at company scale we usually\nhave 1 database, Now problem with having a single DB, If there is only one DB then again there is a similar\nproblem that we were facing with single instance that there are millions of requests and if there are\nmillions of request then this DB will crash. again there is a issue. So we can't have a single DB also.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "gMgD1DgCk589dRs1lwcit",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1491.417911797909,
      "y": 72578.76181213549,
      "width": 231,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
