      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775963553367,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "So How is this solve?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "So How is this solve?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "DqZtADSG2b5fBaHnLT30-",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1538.4949567446104,
      "y": 72612.90748989445,
      "width": 1133,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1835184356,
      "version": 1917,
      "versionNonce": 1229546076,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775964348344,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We understand the DB usecases -> In general we see two type of transaction in a database, one is read\nand another is write, whatever transaction we do on a daily basis in whichever app we interact with\nwhat kind of transactions are high read or write -> read\nLike in amazon we see 10, 20 , 30 product then we shop only 1. So when we are browsing products we\nare doing a read transaction, as a seller when we are updating a product or adding a product that is\na write transaction. When we are purchasing something that is a write transaction on our DB.\nSo how we now devide our DB. one is write DB and one is read DB which is also called as Read replica.\nWrite DB will keep on replicating data on Read DB. We might have seen alot lets say we book a flight\nticket or a movie ticket or something like this, so whenever we are booking so right after booking if \nwe try and see the sheet if still available. It might show us that it is available. Why because it is\nnot updated in the Read DB. But that is not a issue due to when we go and try to book the ticket what\nwill happen is from one of the backend server we will be move to write DB and write DB will show that\nticket is already booked. So at least we are not able to book. So again if we will check the ticket is \nbooked or not and that time it might show us that it is available. Also happen in a lot of flash sale.\nLike in flash sale of anything it shows that the product is available we try and buy and by the time\nproduct is out of stock. Why because the read DB was not updated, but obviously when we try write \noperation, then there is only one write DB and that will show product is out of stock.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We understand the DB usecases -> In general we see two type of transaction in a database, one is read\nand another is write, whatever transaction we do on a daily basis in whichever app we interact with\nwhat kind of transactions are high read or write -> read\nLike in amazon we see 10, 20 , 30 product then we shop only 1. So when we are browsing products we\nare doing a read transaction, as a seller when we are updating a product or adding a product that is\na write transaction. When we are purchasing something that is a write transaction on our DB.\nSo how we now devide our DB. one is write DB and one is read DB which is also called as Read replica.\nWrite DB will keep on replicating data on Read DB. We might have seen alot lets say we book a flight\nticket or a movie ticket or something like this, so whenever we are booking so right after booking if \nwe try and see the sheet if still available. It might show us that it is available. Why because it is\nnot updated in the Read DB. But that is not a issue due to when we go and try to book the ticket what\nwill happen is from one of the backend server we will be move to write DB and write DB will show that\nticket is already booked. So at least we are not able to book. So again if we will check the ticket is \nbooked or not and that time it might show us that it is available. Also happen in a lot of flash sale.\nLike in flash sale of anything it shows that the product is available we try and buy and by the time\nproduct is out of stock. Why because the read DB was not updated, but obviously when we try write \noperation, then there is only one write DB and that will show product is out of stock.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
