      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "we can send the read request to write DB when replication is going on, that we never do, like replica\nwill start after every 10 minute, 10-15 minute is much more, Companies configure it in every 1 or 2\nminute, Like in every 1 or 2 minute, it will keep on sending the additional data, not the whole database.\nSo basically it is the diff between two files. At the end of the day these are also file, so they can\ncheck the diff and set the diff to replica.\n\nMaster-Slave is totally different we will see in big data database. this that we discussed these are our\nregular application's SQL or NOSQL DB.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "we can send the read request to write DB when replication is going on, that we never do, like replica\nwill start after every 10 minute, 10-15 minute is much more, Companies configure it in every 1 or 2\nminute, Like in every 1 or 2 minute, it will keep on sending the additional data, not the whole database.\nSo basically it is the diff between two files. At the end of the day these are also file, so they can\ncheck the diff and set the diff to replica.\n\nMaster-Slave is totally different we will see in big data database. this that we discussed these are our\nregular application's SQL or NOSQL DB.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8C5J6pipDXCVtEBWYRc15",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1563.008544369483,
      "y": 74665.68741903894,
      "width": 1199,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkd",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 586998492,
      "version": 271,
      "versionNonce": 2135433316,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775966951670,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Back ->\nfor this kind of service, there is a database already in Amazon that we can use, service already in \namazon that we can use ,for SQL databases we can use RDS for relational database service. For NOSQL databases\nwe can use DynamoDB.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Back ->\nfor this kind of service, there is a database already in Amazon that we can use, service already in \namazon that we can use ,for SQL databases we can use RDS for relational database service. For NOSQL databases\nwe can use DynamoDB.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Cw8_J3wylOQNBKMqe0uDx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1565.0895010240959,
      "y": 74806.0477409764,
      "width": 1188,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bke",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1526617956,
      "version": 1647,
      "versionNonce": 699605732,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775967816781,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Practical ->\n    Build initial 2-tiers, tier 1 and tier 2, now when we build tier 1 we can have just two instances behind\nour LB, tier 2 again we have 2 instances behine our LB and 1 lambda. OR if we want we can have containers\nover here. For launching container or managing containers without installing docker, like for VM without\nusing virtualBox we have a service called EC2, just like that same, similar configurations but this time\nit would not be launching a VM it will be launching a container so our command on base OS is slightly less\nbut if we have to launch our container, AWS provides a service called as ECS(Elastic container service).\nBut it is not taught separately, if we know EC2 then we automatically know ECS. with ECS there is one\nadditional service that we might use which is called as ECR(Elastic Container Registry). ECR is just like\nour Dockerhub. We can pull images from dockerhub and launch our containers, just like that if we want to\nsave or pull images from our own private registry, we can create our registry in something called as ECR.\nAmazon also provide certain pre design container images from ECR. So we can pull and use those images as\nwell. If we dont want to have it from ECR, we can have container image from S3 bucket as well. I can have\nmy public repo in S3 bucket and we can launch container from their as well.\ndesign in a way that load balancer can auto scale if needed.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Practical ->\n    Build initial 2-tiers, tier 1 and tier 2, now when we build tier 1 we can have just two instances behind\nour LB, tier 2 again we have 2 instances behine our LB and 1 lambda. OR if we want we can have containers\nover here. For launching container or managing containers without installing docker, like for VM without\nusing virtualBox we have a service called EC2, just like that same, similar configurations but this time\nit would not be launching a VM it will be launching a container so our command on base OS is slightly less\nbut if we have to launch our container, AWS provides a service called as ECS(Elastic container service).\nBut it is not taught separately, if we know EC2 then we automatically know ECS. with ECS there is one\nadditional service that we might use which is called as ECR(Elastic Container Registry). ECR is just like\nour Dockerhub. We can pull images from dockerhub and launch our containers, just like that if we want to\nsave or pull images from our own private registry, we can create our registry in something called as ECR.\nAmazon also provide certain pre design container images from ECR. So we can pull and use those images as\nwell. If we dont want to have it from ECR, we can have container image from S3 bucket as well. I can have\nmy public repo in S3 bucket and we can launch container from their as well.\ndesign in a way that load balancer can auto scale if needed.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
