      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775968326021,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "try to setup this simple thing but the database that we are going to make, try to practice on how to \nsetup a read replica of this DB. So when we setup read replica there are various configuration that\nwe give. like how many replica, howmuch time for replication, where we have to create, using this\nwe will understand what kind of parameters can be given. this is staraightforwar, how it works is they\nwill give us SQL installed, this SQL if we are using RDS service, lets say my frontend, backend,database\nare in the same machine. so what we need to do instead of Postgress we need to give RDS endpoint.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "try to setup this simple thing but the database that we are going to make, try to practice on how to \nsetup a read replica of this DB. So when we setup read replica there are various configuration that\nwe give. like how many replica, howmuch time for replication, where we have to create, using this\nwe will understand what kind of parameters can be given. this is staraightforwar, how it works is they\nwill give us SQL installed, this SQL if we are using RDS service, lets say my frontend, backend,database\nare in the same machine. so what we need to do instead of Postgress we need to give RDS endpoint.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4mkKNcTzQGUYNW86OUI1h",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1676.8315585562918,
      "y": 75799.19963560354,
