      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bks",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1026315228,
      "version": 689,
      "versionNonce": 140773596,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775968699470,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Once we are ready with our 3 tier deployment we can use Ebs, we can attach EBS to our frontend machines\nfor the logs and all are connected with S3,same way backend machines EBS attached and S3.\nthis is a highly highly scalable architecture, it can be scale up to millions of users. without having\nany downtime or without having any increased latency.\nthis architecture we generally build for our main service,like in practical we will do for login, but\ngenerally for login we dont build this much.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Once we are ready with our 3 tier deployment we can use Ebs, we can attach EBS to our frontend machines\nfor the logs and all are connected with S3,same way backend machines EBS attached and S3.\nthis is a highly highly scalable architecture, it can be scale up to millions of users. without having\nany downtime or without having any increased latency.\nthis architecture we generally build for our main service,like in practical we will do for login, but\ngenerally for login we dont build this much.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "JxFvZeLIP4142NB2kM5S-",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1676.639407352428,
      "y": 75988.32956841112,
      "width": 1199,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkt",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1210352092,
      "version": 1759,
      "versionNonce": 1796929116,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775969474423,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Main service -> Amazon , main function of this website is to show me or display the product that I search.\nBut there are additional things also for example top product of the day, if we are buying X product, then\nwe are getting product recommendation, we are getting discount recommendation, and for all of this usually\nwhat we have in backend is our ML engine running. so these becomes our ML service1, ML service 2 and so on.\nProblem with these services are we can't deply these in our backend machine, Rationality behind them, these\nare heavy codes, heavy ML algorithms, It will make first of all my backend machine slow, So I can't have them\non my backend machine, second issue if one service is failing or crashed my main pipeline is also being\ndisturbed. that we never want. Third issue because these are heavy we can't deploy on Lambda also, if it is\na small ML service we can have it on Lambda, but it is a heavy ML service or LLM or something like this we \ncan't deploy this on my lambda also. So we need a proper machine for this. Lets say daily users are searching\nsomething based on that I am predicting that what all things are needed or what all they will buy in future,\nfuture buying trends we are predicting. So for this I can't have this written in my backend, I have to write\na separate Machine learning service for this.\n\nMain pipeline is our main business functionality, in context of Amazon, main functionality is to display the \nproducts whatever we want to search and make sure buying happens efficiently. So that becomes part of our \nmain pipeline",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Main service -> Amazon , main function of this website is to show me or display the product that I search.\nBut there are additional things also for example top product of the day, if we are buying X product, then\nwe are getting product recommendation, we are getting discount recommendation, and for all of this usually\nwhat we have in backend is our ML engine running. so these becomes our ML service1, ML service 2 and so on.\nProblem with these services are we can't deply these in our backend machine, Rationality behind them, these\nare heavy codes, heavy ML algorithms, It will make first of all my backend machine slow, So I can't have them\non my backend machine, second issue if one service is failing or crashed my main pipeline is also being\ndisturbed. that we never want. Third issue because these are heavy we can't deploy on Lambda also, if it is\na small ML service we can have it on Lambda, but it is a heavy ML service or LLM or something like this we \ncan't deploy this on my lambda also. So we need a proper machine for this. Lets say daily users are searching\nsomething based on that I am predicting that what all things are needed or what all they will buy in future,\nfuture buying trends we are predicting. So for this I can't have this written in my backend, I have to write\na separate Machine learning service for this.\n\nMain pipeline is our main business functionality, in context of Amazon, main functionality is to display the \nproducts whatever we want to search and make sure buying happens efficiently. So that becomes part of our \nmain pipeline",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
